plan:
To resolve the issue 'vertx-maven-plugin not found', follow these steps:

1. Check if the `vertx-maven-plugin` is included in the project's dependencies.
2. If it's not included, add the plugin to the project's dependencies by adding the following dependency to the pom.xml file:
```
<dependency>
    <groupId>io.vertx</groupId>
    <artifactId>vertx-maven-plugin</artifactId>
    <version>3.9.4</version>
</dependency>
```
3. If you're using Maven 3.6 or later, you may need to add the plugin's repository to your project's settings.xml file:
```
<settings>
    <profiles>
        <profile>
            <id>vertx-maven-plugin</id>
            <activation>
                <activeByDefault>true</activeByDefault>
            </activation>
            <repositories>
                <repository>
                    <id>vertx-repo</id>
                    <name>Vert.x Maven Repository</name>
                    <url>https://maven.vertx.io/repository/maven-public/</url>
                </repository>
            </repositories>
        </profile>
    </profiles>
</settings>
```
4. Run the `mvn clean package` command to rebuild your project.
rationale: The 'vertx-maven-plugin' is required for building Vert.x projects with Maven. If it's not included in the project's dependencies, Maven won't be able to find it and will throw an error. By adding the plugin to the project's dependencies, you ensure that Maven can properly build your project.
